                "name": "Universe",
                "url": "/topics/universe"
            },
            {
                "name": "Kinds",
                "url": "/topics/kinds"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/said_nursi_778023",
        "quote": "Practice the brotherhood, love, and cooperation insistently enjoined by hundreds of Qur'anic verses and traditions of the Prophet!",
        "author": {
            "name": "Said Nursi",
            "url": "/quotes/said_nursi_778023"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Love",
                "url": "/topics/love"
            },
            {
                "name": "Practice",
                "url": "/topics/practice"
            },
            {
                "name": "Brotherhood",
                "url": "/topics/brotherhood"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/said_nursi_778026",
        "quote": "If you look at the Qur'an with the eyes of a sound heart, you will see that its six aspects are so brilliant and transparent that no darkness, no misguidance, no doubt or suspicion, no trickery could enter it or find a fissure through which to enter and violate its purity.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Said Nursi",
            "url": "/quotes/said_nursi_778026"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Sound",
                "url": "/topics/sound"
            },
            {
                "name": "Through",
                "url": "/topics/through"
            },
            {
                "name": "Purity",
                "url": "/topics/purity"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/said_nursi_778033",
        "quote": "The beauty of man's being, fashioned as he is in the fairest of forms, demonstrates the existence of the Maker, while at the same time the fact that, together with his comprehensive abilities, lodged in that fairest of forms, he soon declines and dies, demonstrates the existence of the resurrection.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Said Nursi",
            "url": "/quotes/said_nursi_778033"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Beauty",
                "url": "/topics/beauty"
            },
            {
                "name": "Fact",
                "url": "/topics/fact"
            },
            {
                "name": "Same Time",
                "url": "/topics/same_time"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/said_nursi_778035",
        "quote": "The raising to life of all animate beings at the resurrection of the dead can be no more difficult for Divine Power than restoring to life a fly in the spring, heavy with the death-stained sleep of winter.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Said Nursi",
            "url": "/quotes/said_nursi_778035"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Difficult",
                "url": "/topics/difficult"
            },
            {
                "name": "More",
                "url": "/topics/more"
            },
            {
                "name": "Raising",
                "url": "/topics/raising"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/said_nursi_778036",
        "quote": "The All-Wise Maker attaches hundreds of instances of wisdom to each of the beings in the palace of the universe and equips them to perform hundreds of duties. To all trees He bestows instances of wisdom to the number of its fruits and gives duties to the number of its flowers.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Said Nursi",
            "url": "/quotes/said_nursi_778036"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Flowers",
                "url": "/topics/flowers"
            },
            {
                "name": "Palace",
                "url": "/topics/palace"
            },
            {
                "name": "Perform",
                "url": "/topics/perform"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/said_nursi_778037",
        "quote": "The life of the hereafter is the outcome of all this world.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Said Nursi",
            "url": "/quotes/said_nursi_778037"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Life",
                "url": "/topics/life"
            },
            {
                "name": "World",
                "url": "/topics/world"
            },
            {
                "name": "Hereafter",
                "url": "/topics/hereafter"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/said_nursi_778039",
        "quote": "Something theoretical in the past may become evident and established in the present or in the future. It is a self-evident fact that creation has an innate tendency towards perfection, and it is through this that creation is bound to the law of development or gradual perfection.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Said Nursi",
            "url": "/quotes/said_nursi_778039"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Through",
                "url": "/topics/through"
            },
            {
                "name": "Established",
                "url": "/topics/established"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/said_nursi_778040",
        "quote": "Some sciences need mutual support and assistance to develop. The majority of these are physical sciences. Mutual support has almost no use in other disciplines, such as attainment of intuitive knowledge of God or spiritual progress.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Said Nursi",
            "url": "/quotes/said_nursi_778040"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Need",
                "url": "/topics/need"
            },
            {
                "name": "Some",
                "url": "/topics/some"
            },
            {
                "name": "Other",
                "url": "/topics/other"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/said_nursi_778041",
        "quote": "Those who are greatly occupied in physical or material matters lack sufficient knowledge or have only superficial understanding of spiritual matters. Therefore, such people's opinions and judgments concerning spiritual matters carry no weight.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Said Nursi",
            "url": "/quotes/said_nursi_778041"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "People",
                "url": "/topics/people"
            },
            {
                "name": "Weight",
                "url": "/topics/weight"
            },
            {
                "name": "Judgments",
                "url": "/topics/judgments"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/said_nursi_778042",
        "quote": "Attributing to anything or anyone more good than God has attributed to them is not a positive move, nor does it mean that you have done them any good. A single grain of truth is preferable to a bumper harvest of false imaginings.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Said Nursi",
            "url": "/quotes/said_nursi_778042"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Good",
                "url": "/topics/good"
            },
            {
                "name": "Anything",
                "url": "/topics/anything"
            },
            {
                "name": "Nor",
                "url": "/topics/nor"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/said_nursi_778044",
        "quote": "The divine wisdom which requires a division of labor has sown different abilities and tendencies in human nature and has enabled human beings to carry out the duty of establishing sciences and developing technology. The fulfillment of this duty is obligatory upon humanity as a whole, though not on every individual.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Said Nursi",
            "url": "/quotes/said_nursi_778044"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Whole",
                "url": "/topics/whole"
            },
            {
                "name": "Sown",
                "url": "/topics/sown"
            },
            {
                "name": "Establishing",
                "url": "/topics/establishing"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/said_nursi_778045",
        "quote": "People who do not recognize their Owner and discover their Master are miserable and bewildered. But those who do, and then take refuge in His Mercy and rely on His Power, see this desolate world transformed into a place of rest and felicity, a place of exchange for the Hereafter.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Said Nursi",
            "url": "/quotes/said_nursi_778045"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "World",
                "url": "/topics/world"
            },
            {
                "name": "See",
                "url": "/topics/see"
            },
            {
                "name": "His",
                "url": "/topics/his"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/said_nursi_778014",
        "quote": "There has been no persecution I have not tasted, no oppression I have not suffered. I neither care for Paradise nor fear Hell. If I see my nation's belief secured, I will not even care about burning in Hell, for while my body is burning, my heart will be as if in a rose garden.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Said Nursi",
            "url": "/quotes/said_nursi_778014"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Nation",
                "url": "/topics/nation"
            },
            {
                "name": "About",
                "url": "/topics/about"
            },
            {
                "name": "Been",
                "url": "/topics/been"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/said_nursi_778029",
        "quote": "All true happiness, pure joy, sweet bounties, and untroubled pleasure lie in knowledge of God and love of God; they cannot exist without them.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Said Nursi",
            "url": "/quotes/said_nursi_778029"
        },
